</text-section><text-section><b>ATP Production</b>
</text-section><text-section>Aerobic respiration typically produces a net total of 36 ATP per molecule of glucose consumed
</text-section><text-section><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></text-section><text-section>Hydrogen carriers produce different amounts of ATP depending on where they donate electrons to the transport chain
</text-section><text-section><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></text-section><text-section>Oxidative phosphorylation: (8 matrix NADH) + (2 cytosolic NADH) + (2 FADH) = (8 3) + (2 2) + (2 2) = 32 ATP
